<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--CrowdedBalloon     08-18 0151</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Crowded Balloon,0152</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dutch Balloon Flies With Largest-Ever Group Of Passengers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LELYSTAD, Netherlands (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Dutch hot air balloon took a
record number of 50 people to the skies and landed safely after a
20-minute flight, its captain said.
   Balloonist Henk Brink, his wife Eveline, four crewmen and 44
passengers on Wednesday improved the 1979 record set by Cristopher
Davey of Great Britain, who took off with 31 other people near
Muenster, West Germany.
   ``Everybody enjoyed it immensely,'' Brink told The Associated
Press shortly after touching down smoothly in a field a few miles
from the airfield where he had alighted.
   Brink's 151-foot-high balloon, carrying a twin-level passenger
basket and six propane burners, made the flight at an altitude of
330 feet.
   In 1986, Brink set a speed record for crossing the Atlantic by
balloon, completing the trip from Newfoundland to the Netherlands
in 51 hours and 15 minutes.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
