<2ND_LINE>PM-Drought-No Water,0127</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Small Pa. Town Running Out Of Water</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TIDIOUTE, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   More than 900 households in this
northwestern Pennsylvania are expected to run out of water soon
because of the drought, officials said.
   Water in the Ben George Reservoir along Tidioute Creek, which
normally supplies most of town's water, were expected to drop to
levels below the intake pumps today, Mayor Harvey Weaver said
Wednesday night.
   Three 450-gallon water tanks have been brought to the area.
Authorities in this town 40 miles southeast of Erie also planned to
tap into a test well.
   An advisory for boiling drinking water would be put into effect
because water from the well won't be chlorinated and will be high
in iron and sodium content.
</TEXT>
