<HEAD>NEW ORLEANS: our nation.</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   He came home to head the Central Intelligence Agency where he
strengthened the intelligence community while working to guarantee
the rights of our citizens.
   Through it all, George Bush found time to be a devoted husband
and a loving father to five children and grandfather to 10.
   George Bush is the greatest vice president this nation has ever
had. He has always made us proud.
   When the Soviet Union targeted a new class of nuclear weapons at
Western Europe, destroying the military balance and threatening
peace, Vice President Bush flew to Europe to meet with our NATO
allies.
   Prime Minister Thatcher of Britain, President Mitterrand of
France, Chancellor Kohl of West Germany, and the others. They know
George Bush; they trust him; they respect him.
   And from those meetings came their decision: They would deploy
missiles in Europe.
   The threat was answered, the alliance held and Moscow
understood. And as a result, today we have an INF treaty and the
Soviet missiles are being withdrawn and destroyed. Now, that's what
leadership is about.
   As chairman of the South Florida Task Force, George Bush put
together this nation's first really successful effort to protect
our children from illegal drugs. While Michael Dukakis opposes
mandatory sentencing for the thugs who sell drugs to our children
and opposes the death penalty for drug pushers who murder our
police officers, George Bush knows that the only way you can deal
with drug pushers is to grab them by the throat.
   And with George Bush as our president, that's exactly what we're
going to do.
   Under his leadership we can and will rid America of illegal
drugs.
   America is not a great nation because brilliant and talented
people came to live here. America is a great nation because our
system offers incentives and opportunities for greatness.
   America has produced extraordinary results from plain, ordinary
common people like you and me.
   The genius of America's success lies not in the brilliance of a
few, but in the spirit of enterprise, work and family of all of us
who call ourselves Americans.
   Our program has rekindled that spirit to bring greater
prosperity to more people than ever before. But we have only
scratched the surface of what America can be.
   With George Bush as our president, with Dan Quayle as our vice
president building on the success of the last eight years, there is
no limit to the future of the American people.
   I am honored to place in nomination the name of a man who has
served America in war and in peace, who has the experience, the
character and the strength to lead this great land we love.
   Mr. Chairman, I nominate, for president of the United States,
George Bush of Houston, Texas.
</TEXT>
