<2ND_LINE>PM-Hidden Body,0201</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police: Scared Youths Hid Friend's Body After Accidental Slaying</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three scared brothers hid a teen-age
friend's body in a vacant house for 10 days after an accidental
shotgun blast killed him, police say.
   Preliminary autopsy results performed Wednesday indicated that
William Dennis Bowen III, 14, died of a shotgun wound to the head,
said George Pinckney, a police spokesman.
   Tests were being conducted to determine, among other things,
whether Bowen died instantly, Pickney said.
   After questioning the brothers, ages 12, 14 and 15, authorities
believe the Aug. 7 shooting was an accident, Pinckney said. Bowen
had been reported missing by his parents on Aug. 8.
   No charges have been filed and the investigation continues.
   Names of the brothers were not released because they are
juveniles.
   Bowen's body was discovered Tuesday, after one of the youths
told an adult about it.
   The four had been playing with a shotgun they had found in an
apartment of a relative of the brothers, the youth told police. The
relative wasn't at home. After the weapon discharged, the brothers
stashed Bowen's body in a vacant house next door, police said.
</TEXT>
