Islamic Jihad's statement on the hostages. It was released Thursday
and translated into English by The Associated Press.
   In the name of Allah, the merciful, the compassionate.
   After the increasing talk about the early release of the foreign
hostages, we announce today the following:
   1. What everyone expects soon is a mirage assumed to be water by
a thirsty man.
   2. Counting on regional and international developments will not
be of use at all in releasing the captives in Lebanon.
   3. We are the only side that decides the fate of the captives,
be it at the level of releasing them, executing them or maintaining
their detention.
