<HEAD>One Dead, Eight Injured in Street Shooting</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A shooting at a location known for drug violence
led to a second shooting Thursday, and a young man was killed and
eight people were injured, police said.
   The first shooting, at the Red Hook Housing Projects in
Brooklyn, occurred about 12:23 a.m., police Officer Hugh Barry said.
   An unidentified man was approached by six men who opened fire
with semiautomatic weapons. The victim, in his 20s, was taken to
Methodist Hospital, where he was pronounced dead. A companion was
wounded.
   The site has a history of drug-related violence, Barry said.
   An hour later, two men in a car opened fire on a group of young
people standing outside, wounding seven of them, police said.
   The motive for the first shooting was unknown, but the second
was ``apparently a retaliation for the first,'' according to Barry.
   A 21-year-old woman was hospitalized in critical condition with
a gunshot wound to her right side, Barry said. The other victims
were listed in stable condition or released from hospitals, he said.
</TEXT>
