<1ST_LINE>u i AM-Iran-Rebels 1stLd-Writethru a0829 08-18 0579</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Iran-Rebels, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0829,0594</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Anti-Khomeini Rebels Claim Mass Execution Of Dissidents By Iran</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Gulf Rdp</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS graf 4 `There was...since April' to RESTORE dropped
word, picks up graf 5 `Edward Mortimer...'</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By ED BLANCHE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The main Iranian rebel group claimed
Thursday the government in Tehran has executed thousands of its
activists and supporters in recent weeks and secretly buried them
in mass graves.
   The Mujahedeen Khalq, or People's Holy Warriors, said in a
statement telexed from its headquarters in Baghdad, capital of
Iraq, that most of those killed had spent years in prison.
   It added that hundreds of civilians in western Iran were
publicly hanged for supporting rebel forces that pushed into the
region from bases in Iraq last month.
   There was no independent confirmation of the claim, which the
Mujahedeen Khalq said was based on ``reliable reports from Iran,''
but the Financial Times of London reported from Tehran on Wednesday
that ``systematic executions of left-wing prisoners'' had been
carried out since April.
   Edward Mortimer, the correspondent, said the executions
accelerated after the Mujahedeen Khalq's National Liberation Army
of Iran moved into western Iran after Iran announced July 18 that
it would accept a U.N. Security Council cease-fire resolution.
   Mortimer said families of executed prisoners wre jamming Behesht
Zahra cemetery in Tehran, where the slain were buried in special
plots. He said 58 bodies were buried between July 27 and Aug. 10.
   Some Iranian leaders, including Chief Justice Mussavi Ardebili,
publicly demanded that imprisoned rebels be executed.
   Ardebili said on Tehran radio Aug. 5: ``There is no need for any
trial. The crime is clear ... and the punishment is also clear. I
pray to God that all of them are destroyed.''
   Iran's former revolutionary prosecutor, Habib Ladjevardi,
criticized authorities recently for showing clemency to political
prisoners who repented. Ladjevardi helped send hundreds of alleged
government opponents to their deaths.
   The Mujahedeen statement said Iranian authorities carried out
the mass executions in retaliation for widespread support given the
rebel invaders.
   It said the government's purpose ``is to slow down the process
of its inevitable overthrow, a process that has accelerated in the
wake of the regime's acceptance of the cease-fire.''
   According to the Financial Times, another reason for the
executions was an official ``desire to placate angry radicals after
the cease-fire.''
   Both the paper and the Mujahedeen statement said executions were
most numerous in Kerend in southwest Iran, where townspeople
welcomed the invaders.
   Attacks by Liberation Army into western Iran have increased in
recent months and Iranian leaders have publicly acknowledged rebel
incursions.
   Iran claimed the army killed 4,800 rebels last month and drove
the rest back into Iraq. Its official Islamic Republic News Agency
reported in recent days that scores of captured Mujahedeen fighters
were publicly hanged in several western towns.
   Another Iranian opposition group, the outlawed pro-Moscow Tudeh
Communist Party, said ``group after group'' of Mujahedeen
activists, political prisoners and ``collaborators'' were executed
in the past month.
   The Mujahedeen Khalq was allies of Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini
in the Islamic revolution that ousted the late Shah Mohammad Reza
Pahlavi in February 1979, but the fundamentalists later turned on
the Mujahedeen and other leftist and liberal factions.
   In its latest statement, the rebel group said about 70,000
people have been executed in Iran since Khomeini's revolution.
   Amnesty International, the human rights group based in London,
lists about 6,000 but says it believes the true figure is much
higher.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> AP880818-0235 </DOCNO>
