<HEAD>Heavy Rains Close Interstate 25</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A storm that stalled over the metropolitan area
dumped up to 2 inches of rain Wednesday afternoon, flooding
Interstate 25 with two feet of standing water and closing the
highway at rush hour.
   I-25, the main north-south route through Colorado, bisects the
southern Denver area.
   Mike Baker of the National Weather Service said that at one
measuring point 2 inches of rain fell in a two-hour period, and
most of it within 60 minutes. He said there were other rainfall
reports of .81 within an hour and .54 within an hour in the
metropolitan area.
   Baker said the storm remained stationary over the region for
about an hour.
   Police said roads throughout the area were closed temporarily
and motorists were stranded, but no major accidents were reported.
