<DATELINE>JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A strong earthquake under the Indian
Ocean rocked the Indonesian island of Java on Wednesday, but
officials said no immediate reports were made of injuries or damage.
   The quake registered 6 on the open-ended Richter scale and its
epicenter was about 250 miles north of Jakarta, the capital of
Indonesia, and 21 miles under the surface, the Meteorological
Center said.
   Some Jakarta residents said they felt tremors briefly.
   The Richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on
seismographs. A quake of magnitude 6 can cause severe damage.
