<TEXT>
   In the first uneasy truce in a lengthy
takeover battle, officials of Farmers Insurance Group Inc. and
Batus Inc. have met to discuss Batus' proposal for a friendly $4.9
billion buyout.
   But both sides said they are prepared to continue the war they
have waged for eight months in the courts and before state
regulatory bodies.
   Wednesday's meeting came a day after Farmers agreed to discuss a
sweetened, $72-a-share offer from the Louisville, Ky.,-based
tobacco and retailing company.
