waging a proxy battle that could lead to the sale of the company
her late father founded and estranged husband runs, says there's no
reason to believe the capsule maker's brisk earnings pace will
continue.
   Karla Scherer Fink addressed shareholders Wednesday at the
company's annual meeting in an effort to win three seats on
Scherer's board. The meeting was adjourned until next Wednesday
when results of the balloting would be announced.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>ROCHESTER, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
