household products group it acquired in the $5.1 billion
acquisition of Sterling Drug Co.
   Kodak concluded the Lehn & Fink unit of Sterling, which sells
Lysol disinfectant, D-Con rat poison and other well-known products
``is too important to lose,'' company officials said Wednesday.
   Published reports and rumors recently on Wall Street indicated
Kodak planned to sell the Montvale, N.J.-based unit, which had
sales of $594 million last year.
</TEXT>
