<FILEID>AP-NR-08-18-88 1142EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r f BC-CokeStock     08-18 0118</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Coke Stock,0123</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Coke Selling Preferred Shares</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Coca-Cola Co. plans to raise $300 million through
its first preferred-stock issue.
   In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission on
Wednesday, the soft drink giant said it would sell 100,000 shares
of non-voting ``money market cumulative preferred'' stock at $3,000
a share in four series.
   Although the new shares are described as a money market stock,
the dividend rate is not directly tied to money market
fluctuations. Coca Cola said the rate will be set every 49 days by
bids from stockholders and prospective buyers.
   Proceeds from the issue will be used for general purposes,
including repaying some of its short-term debt, Coca Cola said.
</TEXT>
