compared with last week's 69,533 and last year's 60,405.
   Canadian automakers were to build 17,816 cars this week, up from
12,142 a week ago and up from last year's 6,971.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 17,044,
compared with 17,089 a week ago and 16,267 in the same week last
year.
