<HEAD>Hormel Buys Chicken By George</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AUSTIN, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Geo. A. Hormel & Co. announced Thursday
that it purchased Chicken by George Inc., the Louisville, Ky.,
company founded by former Miss America Phyllis George. The price
was not disclosed.
   Under terms of the agreement, Hormel will acquire all the assets
of Chicken by George and operate the company as a separate division.
   ``This agreement fits well with our company's long-term business
strategies,'' Hormel Chairman R.L. Knowlton said in a statement.
   ``The line of high quality, convenient chicken entrees marketed
by Chicken by George will complement greatly the products currently
produced by our company.''
   Founded by Miss George in 1986, Chicken by George has built a
strong base business in Kentucky with an eight-item line of fresh,
marinated chicken breast entrees.
   Knowlton said Miss George will be actively involved in all
facets of new product development, marketing and promotion for
chicken products as well as an expanded line of beef, pork, fish
and turkey products, all under the By George brand name.
</TEXT>
